---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Product Managers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Product Managers working internationally, covering product management positions abroad, tech product careers, and global product strategy opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Product Managers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Product Managers working abroad, building products internationally, and pursuing careers across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/product-manager-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/product-manager-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Product Manager Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Product Managers define product vision, prioritize features, coordinate cross-functional teams, and drive products from concept to launch. International product management offers opportunities to build products for global markets, lead distributed teams, and develop cross-cultural product expertise.
      </p>
      <p>
        International product management opportunities exist through global tech companies, international startups, multinational enterprises building digital products, and the universal demand for product leadership in technology-driven markets.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Product Managers working abroad across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Product Managers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Product pressure and stakeholder management', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'User research and stakeholder meetings', typical: 'Often needed' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Office-based strategic work', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
          { need: 'Stress management', why: 'Launch pressure and competing priorities', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Wellness programs', why: 'Tech company culture', typical: 'Common at tech companies' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Cross-Functional Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Product managers sit at the intersection of engineering, design, marketing, and business. Managing competing stakeholder demands, making trade-off decisions, and driving alignment across functions creates significant pressure. Mental health support helps navigate this complex organizational role.
      </p>
      <p>
        Product launches create intense pressure periods with high visibility. Balancing feature scope, timeline, and quality while managing expectations requires resilience that benefits from health support infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h3>Tech Industry Benefits</h3>
      <p>
        Product management roles at tech companies typically include comprehensive benefits. Tech companies compete for product talent and offer strong coverage packages. Startup benefits may vary more widely but often include core coverage.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Tech Company</h3>
      <p>
        Large tech product management. Premium tech benefits. Established processes. Tech offers resources.
      </p>

      <h3>Startup</h3>
      <p>
        Early-stage product leadership. Variable startup benefits. Broad scope. Startups offer impact.
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p>
        Corporate product management. Comprehensive enterprise benefits. Complex products. Enterprise offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Agency/Consultancy</h3>
      <p>
        Product consulting. Consultancy benefits. Client variety. Agencies offer breadth.
      </p>

      <h3>Fintech/Healthtech</h3>
      <p>
        Regulated product management. Strong benefits. Domain expertise required. Specialized verticals offer depth.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Product Managers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Product Manager Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Product Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Shipped products. Launch success. Growth delivery. Experience is primary credential.
      </p>

      <h3>Technical Background</h3>
      <p>
        Engineering or technical foundation. Technical fluency. API understanding. Technical background valued.
      </p>

      <h3>Business Understanding</h3>
      <p>
        MBA or business experience. Market analysis. Financial modeling. Business acumen essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Product Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        Product certifications available. AIPMM, Pragmatic. Continuing education. Certifications supplement experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Stakeholder Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Cross-functional coordination. Competing demands. Trade-off decisions. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Launch Intensity</h3>
      <p>
        Product launch pressure. High visibility moments. Feature cuts. Stress management important.
      </p>

      <h3>Office Work</h3>
      <p>
        Strategy development. Roadmap planning. Meeting intensive. Ergonomic coverage relevant.
      </p>

      <h3>User Research Travel</h3>
      <p>
        Customer visits. User interviews. Market research. Travel coverage valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Product Strategy</h3>
      <p>
        Vision setting. Roadmap development. Prioritization frameworks. Strategy guides product.
      </p>

      <h3>Cross-Functional Leadership</h3>
      <p>
        Engineering coordination. Design collaboration. Marketing alignment. Leadership without authority.
      </p>

      <h3>User Focus</h3>
      <p>
        User research. Customer feedback. Problem discovery. Users guide decisions.
      </p>

      <h3>Execution</h3>
      <p>
        Sprint planning. Feature delivery. Launch coordination. Execution realizes vision.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>High Demand Role</h3>
      <p>
        Product management in demand. Tech growth driving need. Global opportunities abundant. Market strong.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior product manager. Director of product. VP product. Chief product officer. Clear progression.
      </p>

      <h3>Technical vs Business</h3>
      <p>
        Technical PM track available. Business-focused PM path. Platform vs consumer. Multiple specializations.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote Friendly</h3>
      <p>
        Product work increasingly remote. Distributed teams common. Async collaboration growing. Remote viable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a product manager considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Tech employers typically provide comprehensive benefits. Remote work increasingly common. International experience valued.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Tech companies yes. Startup coverage varies. Enterprise packages comprehensive. Verify specific offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for product pressure. Stakeholder management intense. Launch stress significant. Support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do product skills transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Core skills yes. User research methods universal. Market context differs. Skills transfer well.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Can I work remotely as a product manager?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Increasingly yes. Distributed teams common. Video collaboration standard. Remote opportunities growing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong demand continues. Tech growth driving need. AI/ML PM emerging. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Consider mental health coverage for stakeholder pressure. Ensure travel coverage for user research. Verify international coverage scope for relocation or remote work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Product Managers build products worldwide. Your coverage should support product careers—addressing cross-functional demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across product management work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Product Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across tech companies, startups, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
